      "id": "intro",
      "number": 1,
      "title": "Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Russian uses the Cyrillic alphabet and <strong>six cases</strong>. Nouns have gender (masculine, feminine, neuter) and adjectives agree with nouns."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "variant": "compare-en",
          "text": "🇬🇧 English word order is mostly fixed (Subject–Verb–Object). Both Kazakh and Russian allow more flexible order because suffixes show grammatical roles."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "pronouns",
